...
17.  Shift4 also agreed that, if the integration was not completed by December 31, 2018,
it would not market its services to CardConnect ISOs. (Isaacman Dep. 86:2-87:23.)

18. Yet, by August 2018 - and despite not having an integration to the FDC North
platform - Shift4 began a targeted campaign of **misleading** CardConnect ISOs into believing
that the integration had, in fact, been completed.

19. For instance, on or around August 10, 2018, Shift4 released a marketing piece
announcing the "completion" of the integration. A true and correct copy of the marketing piece
is attached as Exhibit B.

20.  The marketing piece was blasted out to CardConnect ISOs, despite the fact that
Shift4 knew at the time, that it could not properly service them at all. (Isaacman Dep. 118:1-119:5.)

21. In fact, Shift4's CEO Jered Isaacman admitted the campaign was premature, and
that Shift4 would not be able to convert CardConnect ISOs that responded to the
advertisement:
...

...
Q. All right. And I believe that you had testified earlier that
you thought that the distribution or the sending of that blast email
to CardConnect ISOs and agents at that time was premature:
correct?
A. Yes.
Q. Okay. And you also agreed, I believe, that when an ISO or
agent received that email, that Shift4 would not actually be able
to convert them onto the Shift4 network; correct?
A. That's correct.
